OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOne in four have accents   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fmocked at work - survey    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Almost half of UK workers have had     
OL,6, their accents mocked, criticised or    
OL,7, singled out in a social setting, a     
OL,8, survey suggests.                       
OL,10,FThe Sutton Trust found 46% of workers  
OL,11,Fhave faced jibes about their accents,  
OL,12,Fwith 25% reporting jokes at work.      
OL,14,FAn entrenched "hierarchy of accent"    
OL,15,Fcaused social anxiety throughout some  
OL,16,Fpeople's lives, researchers said.      
OL,18,FThey said those with northern English  
OL,19,For Midlands accents were more likely to
OL,20,Fworry about the way they spoke.        
